<PageTitle>Science - Ananda Marga Fasting Calendar</PageTitle>
<h3>TL;DR</h3>
<p>
    The fasting dates are based on the solar day (sunrise to sunrise) which occurs closest to the relevant tithis (ekádashii, amávasyá and púrńimá).
    Astronomical dawn is considered the start of the day, and the Asia/Kolkata (Varanasi) time zone is used to determine the fasting day.
    In other words, the ekádashii, amávasyá or púrńimá which occurs closest to the solar day in Varanasi (based on astronomical dawn) is the selected fasting day - according to this software.
    This software uses astronomy libraries to calculate the lunar phases used (called thithis) for picking the fasting dates.
</p>
<p>
